Nedbank Helps Rand Water of South Africa Raise $70 Million in Bond Sale

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-04-26T11:35:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/nedbank-helps-rand-water-of-south-africa-raise-70-million-in-bond-sale.html
Nedbank Group Ltd. (NED) ’s investment
banking unit helped Rand Water,  South Africa ’s largest water
board, raise 468 million rand in a switch auction, the
Johannesburg-based lender said.  A total of 425 million rand’s worth of Rand Water’s RWO2
notes were switched for 468 million rand of RW21 bonds, Nedbank
Capital said. The switch auction was Rand Water’s first under a
5 billion rand Domestic Medium Term Note program listed on the
 Johannesburg Stock Exchange , it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  